                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d212">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Eustis</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Gresham</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1894-07-02">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 2, 1894</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>President Carnot’s funeral yesterday was very imposing, and as a tribute of the
                    national grief was worthy of France. The whole ceremony lasted six hours. The
                    cost of floral wreaths, exceeded 2,000,000 francs. The popular demonstration was
                    most orderly, respectful, and sympathetic.</p>
                <p>Though not well, and the heat was intense, I accompanied the cortege on foot. His
                    remains rest in the Pantheon.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Eustis</hi>,</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
